Course Description and Objectives:
Tai Chi is an ancient Chinese martial art‚Ä¶ but its emphasis is not the harming of an adversary‚Ä¶ what it does emphasize is strengthening yourself. Tai Chi movement is gentle, relaxed, peaceful and fluid, it provides self healing, clarity, and balance to those who practice its principles regularly. By relaxing tension and practicing balance, the enormous natural strength of our bodies can be restored. 

There are many aspects to the practice of Tai Chi. In this course we will learn: 

To use our bodies and minds in a way that is natural and balanced. 
Tai Chi form, a series of gentle movements that provides a structure for practicing Tai Chi principles.
Standing Chi Kung, a set of postures to realign your body.
Pushing Hands, a practice done with a partner where you learn to sense balance and neutralize incoming and outgoing energies.
Exercises to remove blockages from your body, emotions, mind. etc.
Breathing exercises, relaxation exercises, meditation, awareness expansion, energy circulation exercises.

Course Objectives:
By the completion of this course students will have:

A daily Tai Chi practice routine that can be varied to the needs of that day.
Understanding of Tai Chi principles that will continue to unfold and deepen long after this course is completed.
More often be happy, balanced, peaceful and strong.
A greater understanding of the practical physical mechanics and function of their own body including joint alignment, posture, and breathing.
The ability to be present with and better deal with stress and stressful situations.
